        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 11:28PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 1128 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Statesville, or 6 miles east of Troutman, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mount Ulla, Piedmont Research Station, Woodleaf, Cleveland, Cool
Springs, Cooleemee, and Statesville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
